Template: journald-archive/loopback_size_gib
Type: string
Description: Archive loopback file size, in GiB:
 journald-archive stores compressed journals in a btrfs loopback file
 mounted at /var/log/journal_archive/. This is the maximum *physical*
 size on disk that the archive can ever occupy.
 .
 The suggested default has been computed from the current size of
 /var/log/journal/, assuming a conservative 5x btrfs zstd compression
 ratio. Increase it if you want room for more history; decrease only
 if disk space is tight.

Template: journald-archive/vacuum_size_gib
Type: string
Description: Archive logical retention limit, in GiB:
 `journalctl --vacuum-size` controls how much *uncompressed* journal
 data to keep in the archive. Because btrfs typically compresses
 journals 5-10x, this can safely be larger than the loopback size.
 .
 If the actual compression ratio turns out worse than expected, vacuum
 will trigger sooner; the loopback file size is the hard physical cap.
 .
 Default: 5x the loopback size.

Template: journald-archive/invalid_size
Type: error
Description: A positive whole number is required
 The size must be a positive whole number of GiB, with no units or other
 characters (for example: 2). Please try again.
